    Let <fr:tex>S</fr:tex> be a smooth separated scheme, and <fr:tex>f \colon  X \to  S</fr:tex> a smooth proper morphism.
  </fr:p>
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;i. &quot;">
      In rational cohomology, the Leray spectral sequence
      <fr:tex
display="block">         E_2^{pq}         =  \operatorname {H} ^p(S, \operatorname {R} ^qf_* \mathbb {Q} )          \Rightarrow   \operatorname {H} ^{p+q}(X, \mathbb {Q} )       </fr:tex>
      degenerates (<fr:tex>E_2=E_ \infty</fr:tex>).
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;ii. &quot;">
      If <fr:tex>\bar {X}</fr:tex> is a non-singular compactification of <fr:tex>X</fr:tex>, then the canonical morphism
      <fr:tex
display="block">          \operatorname {H} ^n( \bar {X}, \mathbb {Q} )          \to   \operatorname {H} ^0(S, \operatorname {R} ^nf_* \mathbb {Q} )       </fr:tex>
      is surjective.
    </html:li>

  </html:ol>

  
    
    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>260</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.1.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>
      For <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> smooth and projective, claim (i) is proven in <fr:link
href="D1968.xml"
type="local"
addr="D1968">D1968</fr:link>.
      The proof in <fr:link
href="D1968.xml"
type="local"
addr="D1968">D1968</fr:link> is rewritten in a more readable manner in <fr:link
href="G1970.xml"
type="local"
addr="G1970">G1970</fr:link>;
      it does not use the smoothness of <fr:tex>S</fr:tex>.
    </fr:p>

    <fr:p>
      Let us fix <fr:tex>f</fr:tex>, and prove that (i)<fr:tex>\implies</fr:tex>(ii).
    </fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  
